Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics): The paper discusses the development and evaluation of autonomous vehicles, which falls under the domain of robotics. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper discusses various aspects related to the assurance of autonomous vehicles, such as safety requirements, formal verification, and standards and guidelines, which are all related to software engineering. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses security-informed safety analysis and defense in depth and diversity, which are related to cybersecurity and fall under the domain of cryptography and security. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper discusses resilience and safety requirements, open systems perspective, and simulation and dynamic testing, which are related to the design and control of complex systems and fall under the domain of systems and control. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper discusses formal verification and static analysis of ML systems, which are related to the development and evaluation of AI systems and fall under the domain of artificial intelligence.
